title: Biggest protest in Romania since Ceausescu was executed
text: Thousands take to the streets of Bucharest in the biggest anti-government protests in Romania since communist dictator Nicolae Ceausescu was executed Up to 50,000 gathered outside government building in Bucharest and 20,000 in other Romanian cities today It was the biggest since days of Nicolae Ceausescu, who was tried by a kangaroo court and executed in 1989 Today's marches were the 13th consecutive day of protests after attempt to water down corruption penalties Justice minister has already resigned but people are demanding that the entire government now stand down Published: 23:19 GMT, 12 February 2017 | Updated: 03:43 GMT, 13 February 2017 41 shares
